place.name: SWAFIELD
place.gazetteerText: SWAFIELD, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; 2 miles N by E of North Walsham r. station. Post town, North Walsham, under Norwich. Acres, 826. Real property, £1,666. Pop., 172. Houses, 43. S-Hall is the seat of T. Dolphin, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £200.* Patron, the Duchy of Lancaster. The church is ancient. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
